<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BiggerKnife     11-30 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bigger Knife,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Would-be Victim Pulls Bigger Knife On Holdup Suspect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convenience store robbery was thwarted
when a clerk pulled out a bigger knife than her assailant was
brandishing, police say.
   ``She was just like Crocodile Dundee,'' said police Capt. Richard
Higgins, referring to the popular movie character who runs off a
mugger by displaying a large knife.
   The robbery attempt occurred early Monday when two men entered
the convenience store and demanded money from Aleshia Melton, the
lone clerk on duty, police said.
   One of the men held a knife and threatened to cut Ms. Melton, but
she pulled out a foot-long machete and the men fled, Higgins said.
   Higgins said Michael E. Rogers, 27, of Jackson, was arrested near
the store and charged with attempted armed robbery.
   Another cashier brought the machete to the store following a
robbery three months ago, a store employee said.
</TEXT>
