<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--AbortedEscape     11-30 0169</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Aborted Escape,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Prisoners' Daredevil Escape Try Fails</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NUEVO LAREDO, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two inmates used makeshift hang
gliders in a daring escape attempt from a Mexican prison, but they
crashed before getting off prison grounds, an official said.
   Inmate Juan De Dios Gonzalez plunged to the roof of the workshop
at La Loma Prison on Monday and was hospitalized in critical
condition with head and internal injuries, said Arturo Aguilar,
prison director.
   The men had climbed to the roof of the three-story prison and
assembled hang gliders made from pieces of cloth, wood and plastic,
Aguilar said.
   Gonzalez, serving a seven-year sentence for drug possession, and
inmate Jose Contreras took a running start and jumped off the roof,
officials said.
   Contreras, awaiting trial on theft charges, hit a wire fence and
fell 30 feet to the ground. He was hospitalized in fair condition
with broken ribs and a broken leg.
   A third inmate was captured as he clutched his hang glider on the
compound's roof, Aguilar said.
</TEXT>
