<TEXT>
   More than 1,200 broadcast journalists
began a nationwide strike Wednesday against the Finnish Broadcasting
Company.
   The radio and TV reporters in the state-owned company demanded a
9 percent wage increase, but management offered only 2.6 percent.
   The strike does not affect satellite or cable television
broadcasts or commercial radio.
   The commercial TV company, which buys time on the two national
