<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Vatican-AIDS     11-30 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Vatican-AIDS,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Vatican to Hold Conference on AIDS</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Vatican plans to hold a major conference
on AIDS next year, a top church official said Wednesday.
   The conference will deal with scientific, social and ethical
aspects of AIDS, said Archbishop Fiorenzo Angelini, who is charge of
health issues for the Vatican.
   Scientists, health workers, political officials and theologians
are expected to attend the meeting, which will last about two weeks
in November 1989.
   In a major statement on AIDS, the Vatican said in March that what
the Roman Catholic church considers ethically aberrant behavior must
be avoided and that using condoms ignores the issue of sexual
permissiveness, which it called ``the true cause'' of the disease.
   The Vatican, which counsels Catholics to abstain from sexual
practices outside marriage, condemns the use of condoms under any
circumstance.
</TEXT>
