<HEAD>Cassani To Relinquish Vice Chairmanship Of IBM</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kaspar V. Cassani, one of two vice chairmen at
International Business Machines Corp., is relinquishing the
second-ranking job in anticipation of his retirement next year, IBM
said Wednesday.
   IBM also said C. Michael Armstrong, a senior vice president, had
been named to IBM's management committee, the corporation's senior
executive committee, and would return to the United States from
Paris.
   It said David E. McKinney, another senior vice president, would
become president and chief executive of the IBM World Trade
Europe-Middle East-Africa Corp., based in Paris.
   Cassani, who will return to Europe, continues as chairman and
president of IBM World Trade Corp. He was named vice chairman
earlier this year along with Jack D. Kuehler.
</TEXT>
