<2ND_LINE>AM-Gorbachev-NYSE,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gorbachev is Welcome at NYSE, Spokesman Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev is welcome at
the New York Stock Exchange if he can fit a visit into his schedule
next week, a spokesman for the exchange said Wednesday.
   ``He would be very welcome here, by the exchange and the American
business community,'' said Richard Torrenzano, a senior vice
president of the NYSE.
   He said Soviet officials have discussed the possibility of a
visit with NYSE officials. Gorbachev is said to be interested, but
might not have time, he added.
   Torrenzano said that if the Soviet leader visits he would be
offered a chance to ring the stock exchange bell, providing he was
there for the market's 9:30 a.m. EST opening or the 4 p.m. close.
</TEXT>
