<1ST_LINE>r f AM-InvestorsDaily     11-30 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Investors Daily,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Editor Resigns, Managing Editor Promoted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stephen Fox resigned as president, chief
executive officer and editor of Investor's Daily and Wesley Mann is
the new editor of the national financial newspaper, it was announced
Wednesday.
   It was uncertain whether the titles of president and chief
executive officer would be filled, said Mann, who moved up from
managing editor upon Fox's resignation Monday.
   Fox is joining a consulting firm specializing in news media
relations and crisis communications, Mann said. Fox began at
Investor's Daily in 1983 and helped shape it for initial publication
in April 1984.
   Prior to that, Fox was a business writer for the Associated Press
in Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
